-- a `limit` on the source SELECT is effective: only 2 rows are inserted
2
-- a `filter` on the source SELECT is effective: only rows with x >= 7 are inserted
3
7
8
9
-- a construction setting in a nested subquery of the source is effective for that subquery
2
-- a construction setting on the INSERT statement itself does not propagate to the SELECT (all 10 rows)
10
-- a non-construction setting on INSERT ... SELECT still works (all 10 rows)
10
-- an explicit LIMIT clause in the source SELECT still works
3
-- CREATE ... AS SELECT with a construction setting on the SELECT is effective (9 rows: x > 0)
9
-- CREATE ... AS SELECT without construction settings still works (all 10 rows)
10
